{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774403052,"nonce":"n/wvdaIduN9dSFyj0jGgJjZfvhY=","message":"**Update: APT + adaptive control cost results (session 31fa1977)**\n\nPhase 5 (APT + loss_update) results are in. Clean evaluation at pert_scale=0:\n\n| Condition | vel@SISU=0 | vel@SISU=1 | Δvel |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| baseline (pert_std=0, no training perts) | 5.691 | 5.052 | -0.639 (-11%) |\n| standard (pert_std=1) | 3.329 | 3.323 | -0.007 (\u003c-0.2%) |\n| APT (pert_std=1, no loss_update) | 3.316 | 3.308 | -0.007 (\u003c-0.2%) |\n| std+update r=0.3 pert_std=1 | 2.421 | 2.425 | +0.005 (+0.2%) |\n| std+update r=0.3 pert_std=10 | 2.428 | 2.443 | +0.015 (+0.6%) |\n| APT+update r=0.3 pert_std=1 | 2.156 | 2.230 | +0.074 (+3.4%) |\n| APT+update r=0.3 pert_std=10 | 2.429 | 2.441 | +0.012 (+0.5%) |\n\n**Key findings:**\n\n1. The pert_std=0 baseline shows a LARGE (-11%) SISU→velocity effect, but in the WRONG direction (slower at SISU=1). This is anomalous: SISU carried zero information during training (pert amplitude = pert_std × β = 0 × β = 0 always). The network should not have learned any SISU-conditional behavior. Possible explanations: gradient noise creating spurious correlations, or the SISU input acting as a bias/scaling signal that shifts the network's operating point without any learned association.\n\n2. ALL perturbation-trained models collapse SISU→velocity to \u003c1%. The one outlier (APT+update r=0.3 pert_std=1 at +3.4%) appears to be a convergence artifact (its overall velocity is anomalously low at 2.156 vs ~2.4 for other conditions).\n\n3. The SISU sweep (Analysis 2) at pert_scale=0 shows essentially flat velocity profiles across SISU=0 to 1 for all perturbation-trained models.\n\n**Open questions requiring further analysis:**\n- Why does pert_std=0 show SISU dependence? Need to verify this isn't a bug in the evaluation or training pipeline.\n- Can we demonstrate SISU has no robustness benefit? Proposed test: eval with perturbation present, SISU fixed at 0 vs 1 — if performance identical, SISU is unused.\n- Mechanistic analysis: PCA/null-space analysis of GRU hidden states at different SISU values to determine whether SISU modulates task-relevant or task-irrelevant dynamics.\n\nOpus and Gemini research agents analyzing architectural and training modifications that might produce the velocity signature.","files":null}]}